WHAT IT IS
----------

A plugin containing elements and a supporting library for parsing and rendering subtitles encoded using the EBU-TT-D[1] profile of TTML[2].

There are two elements: a parser and a render. The parser is an extended versions of the existing GStreamer subparse element, and the renderer is a modified version of the esisting textoverlay element, both of which are part of the gst-plugins-base plugin set.

[1] https://tech.ebu.ch/docs/tech/tech3380.pdf
[2] http://www.w3.org/TR/ttml1/


HOW TO USE IT
-------------

An example pipeline that plays a DASH stream containing an EBU-TT-D subtitle component is as follows:

gst-launch-1.0 souphttpsrc location=<URL of DASH MPD> ! dashdemux name=d
    ttmlrender name=r d. ! video/quicktime ! queue ! qtdemux ! h264parse !
    avdec_h264 ! autovideoconvert ! videoscale !
    video/x-raw,width=1280,height=720 ! r.video_sink d. ! audio/x-m4a ! queue !
    qtdemux ! aacparse ! avdec_aac ! audioconvert ! alsasink d. ! queue !
    qtdemux ! ttmlparse ! r.text_sink r. ! ximagesink

